{
    "analysis": "The prior Executor output produced full-file group summaries and highlighted large diskio/socket signals, but most of those top groups (e.g., ts-admin-basic-info-service, ts-voucher-service, ts-travel-mongo) are NOT in the predefined list of possible root-cause components (ts-auth-service, ts-order-service, ts-route-service, ts-train-service, ts-travel-service). According to the diagnosis rules, we must restrict root-cause search to those five services. Before declaring a root cause, we need to know whether any of those five services exhibit anomalous metric/trace/log behavior inside the incident window when compared to their global P95 thresholds (thresholds already computed from the full series). If none of the five show anomalies, we must widen detection criteria or re-examine other signals (traces/logs). Next we should extract, for only the five candidate services, the incident-window data and report anomalies where value > global_p95 (for metrics/traces/logs). Return compact aggregates (count in window, anomalies count, earliest anomaly timestamp, max value in window, global_p95) and indicate if a candidate has no data in the window.",
